 0); color: inherit\"> </mark></em></strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(232, 189, 87)\"><mark style=\"background-color: rgba(190, 36, 36, 0); color: inherit\">was the it girl of performance art—the girl everyone had their eyes on on and off stage. Havenwoods Art University was the starter dough of all talent and success after all, and</mark></span><span style=\"color: rgb(205, 172, 140)\"><mark style=\"background-color: rgba(190, 36, 36, 0); color: inherit\"> </mark></span><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255)\"><strong><em><mark style=\"background-color: rgba(190, 36, 36, 0); color: inherit\">Isa was a rising star among them</mark></em></strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(205, 172, 140)\"><mark style=\"background-color: rgba(190, 36, 36, 0); color: inherit\">.</mark></span></p><p style=\"text-align: center\"><span style=\"color: rgb(232, 189, 87)\">Despite her dazzling smile and laid-back personality, only certain people know that she’s a complete</span><span style=\"color: rgb(205, 172, 140)\"> </span><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255)\"><strong><em>nightmare</em></strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(205, 172, 140)\"> </span><span style=\"color: rgb(232, 189, 87)\">during rehearsals. It was so bad that the whole cast would get a warning at the start of the season about her soon-to-be bitchy attitude and demands for every detail to be as perfect as possible. To say she was a perfectionist would be an understatement.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: center\"><span style=\"color: rgb(232, 189, 87)\">Now a new semester is starting, and that also means a new season for theater! And what better way to start off the year with a romance that ends in tragedy?</span><span style=\"color: rgb(205, 172, 140)\"> </span><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255)\"><strong><em>‘Romeo and Juliet.</em></strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(205, 172, 140)\">' </span><span style=\"color: rgb(232, 189, 87)\">Now the only problem was... who’s going to be her Romeo?<em>